    <permalink>1a7a1d_8774d3</permalink>
    <tag>技术元素,3D打印,基础,概念</tag>
    <ip>121.33.190.182</ip>
    <cctype>2</cctype>
    <content><![CDATA[<p>这一篇是本周的周报，是根据刘利刚老师的PPT中的相关内容加以整理和拓展的，算是在这个博客第一篇关于研究生时期的研究方向的日志吧。</p><ul><li><p><b>三维物体的表达方式</b></p></li></ul><p><b>1.Point Cloud(点阵云)</b></p><p>Point cloud is a set of vertices in a three-dimensional coordinate system. These vertices are usually defined b X, Y, and Z coordinates, and typically are intended to be representative of the external surface of an object.</p><p>Point clouds are most often created by 3D scanners and ar used for many purposes, including to create 3D CAD models for manufactured parts metrology/quality inspection, etc.</p><p><b>2.Polygonal Mesh（多边形网格）</b></p><p>A polygon mesh is a collection of vertices, edges and faces that defines the shape of a polyhedral object in 3D computer graphics and solid modeling. The faces usually consist of triangles, quadrilaterals or other simple convex polygons, since this simplifies rendering, but may also be composed of more general concave polygons, or polygons with holes.</p><p>The study of polygon meshes is a large sub-field of computer graphics and geometric modeling. Different representations of polygon meshes are used for different applications and goals. The variety of operations performed on meshes may include Boolean logic, smoothing, simplification, and many others. Network representations,&nbsp;&quot;streaming&quot; and &quot;progressive&quot; meshes, are used to transmit polygon meshes over a network. Volumetric meshes are distinct from polygon meshes in that they explicitly represent both the surface and volume of a structure, while polygon meshes only explicitly represent the surface (the volume is implicit). As polygonal meshes are extensively used in computer graphics, algorithms also exist for ray tracing, collision detection, and rigid-body dynamics of polygon meshes.</p><p><b>3.Implicit Surface（隐式曲面）</b></p><p>An implicit surface is a surface defined by a function over all of space.实际上就是一个函数在空间中张成的封闭曲面，可以用这种方式来建模（例如火焰和烟雾）。这个部分似乎挺重要的，后面会再深入了解一下。</p><p><b>4.Volumetric Data</b></p><p>Volumetric data images are nothing like the depth of field effect known from 2D screens. Nor are they similar to the fake 3D seen in some movie releases. These displays utilize up to thousands of lasers in a complete surround effect, comprising an actual holographic 3D image.</p><p>Volumetric data has found extensive use in medical applications such as 3D CAT scans and MRI's. Other fields putting the technology to use include geological surveying, security scanning and, potentially, 3D gaming.</p><p><b>5.CSG(Constructive Solid Geometry，构造实体几何)</b></p><p>Constructive solid geometry (CSG) is a technique used in solid modeling. Constructive solid geometry allows a modeler to create a complex surface or object by using Boolean operators to combine objects. Often CSG presents a model or surface that appears visually complex, but is actually little more than cleverly combined or decombined objects.</p><p>In 3D computer graphics and CAD CSG is often used in procedural modeling. CSG can also be performed on polygonal meshes, and may or may not be procedural and/or parametric.</p><ul><li><p><b>数字几何处理的流水线</b></p></li></ul><p>1.Input Data（输入数据）</p><p>2.Range-Scan CAD Tomography（层面X线照相术）</p><p>3.Analysis of surface quality（分析表面质量）</p><p>4.Surface smoothing for noise removal（为去噪进行表面平滑）</p><p>5.Parameterization（参数化）</p><p>6.Simplification for complexity reduction（简化复杂度）</p><p>7.Remeshing for improving mesh quality（为提高质量重新进行网格分割）</p><p>8.Freeform and multiresolution modeling（自由变换分辨率与形状）</p><ul><li><p>刘利刚老师的相关研究工作</p></li></ul><p>1.Geometric Modeling（几何建模）</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; a)Arterial Snakes [Siggraph Asia 2010]</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; b)Photo-inspired modeling [Siggragh 2011]</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; c)Scanning using kinects [IEEE TVCG 2012]</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; d)House modeling from LiDAR data [Siggraph 2013]</p><p>2.Mesh Manipulation and Optimization（网格操作与优化）</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; a)Global Laplacian optimization [CAD 2007]</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; b)Dual Laplacian manipulation [CASA 2007]</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; c)Delaunay triangulation [CAGD 2010,2011]</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; d)Blue noise sampling [IEEE TVCG 2012]</p><p>3.Shape Understanding and Analysis（形状理解与分析）</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; a)Sketching mesh cutting [Eurographics2006, 2011]</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; b)Symmetry analysis [Siggraph Asia 2009,2012]</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; c)Feature-aligned texturing [Siggraph Asia 2009]</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; d)Mesh Saliency [GMoD 2013]</p><p>4.Geometry-driven Image（几何驱动的图像修改）</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; a)Parametric human reshaping [Siggraph 210]</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; b)Optimizing photo composition [Eurographics 2010]</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; c)Image retargeting [CGI 2010]</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; d)Image stippling [SMI 2011]</p><p>5.Image and Video Processing（图像、视频处理）</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; a)Animating line drawing [Siggraph Asia 2011]</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; b)Virtual try-on [IEEE CG&amp;A 2012]</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; c)Color to gray [CGI 2012]</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; d)Stop motion animation [IEEE CG&amp;A 2013]</p><p>6.Compressive Sensing in Geometry Processing </p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; a)Feature preserving smoothing [Chinagraph 2012]</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; b)Co-segmentation of 3D shapes [SGP 2012]</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; c)Upright orientation [GMP 2012]</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; d)Decoupling feature and noise [ACM ToG 2013]</p><ul><li><p><b>3D打印的流水线</b></p></li></ul><p>从CAD Model最终成为3D Object需要以下几步：</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;1.3D CAD Model</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2.STL File</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;3.Slicing Software</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;4.Layer Slicing &amp; Tool Path</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;5.3D Printer</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;6.3D Object</p><ul><li><p><b>可以进行的研究方向</b><br /></p></li></ul><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;1.Cost-effective Printing of 3D Object with skin-truss（本质就是通过特殊的结构，在保证制品外观不变的同时，减少需要使用的材料重量，节约成本）</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2.Fast Printing</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;3.Supporting Structure（保证打印出来的制品可以自己立起来）</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;4.Adaptive Hollowing</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;5.Segmentation and Packing</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;6.Path Planning（slicing algorithm）</p><ul><li><p><b>面临的挑战</b></p></li></ul><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 1.傻瓜式设计</p><p>现在的3D打印基本上还是需要CAD软件来进行设计的，但是这对于初学者和没有CAD经验的设计师来说，实际上是非常难以把脑中的创意转换成电脑可以识别的格式的，所以如何可以开发出一款能够让设计更加自然的软件，一定非常有前途。</p><p>现在我的想法是可以通过模拟点阵云的方式，制作出一个10x10x10的立方体模型，每一层有100个点，一共有十层，这些点可以在一定范围内自由移动，所以设计师可以在实体模型上进行设计，之后因为点是确定的，可以方便扫描到电脑中，然后再进行微调，就可以让设计变得轻松直观方便。</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2.宜人型材料</p><p>这个可能暂时我们没办法做，毕竟我们不是学材料的。</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 3.一键式操作</p><p>另一个问题就是即使是设计好了，真正打印出来并不是那么简单，如果能像在普通打印店里面那样点击一下打印就等出品就好了，我觉得这也是一个努力的方向。</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 4.平民化价格</p><p>这个也是我们没办法左右的，可以做的就是利用算法是的原料的使用效率尽可能高。</p>]]></content>
